TY  - JOUR
TI  - Platform Content Moderation and Freedom of Expression in Indonesia: A Legal Analysis
AU  - Santoso, Budi
AU  - Rahman, Ayu
PY  - 2023
JO  - Asian Journal of Law and Society
VL  - 10
IS  - 2
SP  - 145
EP  - 168
DO  - 10.1017/als.2023.001
AB  - This article examines how Indonesian law regulates content moderation practices of major social media platforms, particularly in the context of the Electronic Information and Transactions Law (UU ITE). We analyze the tension between state-mandated content removal and constitutional guarantees of freedom of expression. Findings reveal that Big Tech companies often self-regulate beyond legal requirements, raising concerns about private censorship and digital rights in Indonesia.
KW  - content moderation; Indonesia; freedom of expression; UU ITE; platform governance
