PY  - 2022
JO  - Journal of Malaysian and Comparative Law
VL  - 49
IS  - 1
SP  - 89
EP  - 112
AB  - This study investigates the regulatory framework governing hate speech on social media platforms in Malaysia, focusing on the Communications and Multimedia Act 1998. We assess how platforms like Facebook and Twitter comply with Malaysian law and engage in self-regulatory practices. The paper argues that current legal frameworks inadequately protect freedom of expression while failing to effectively curb harmful content.
KW  - hate speech; Malaysia; social media; self-regulation; CMA 1998
DO  - 10.22452/jmcl.2022.001
