PY  - 2023
JO  - Philippine Law Journal
VL  - 96
IS  - 3
SP  - 201
EP  - 234
AB  - The 2022 Philippine presidential elections highlighted the critical role of social media platforms in the spread of political disinformation. This article analyzes the legal accountability mechanisms available against platforms under Philippine law, including the Cybercrime Prevention Act and proposed platform liability bills. We argue that existing frameworks are insufficient to hold Big Tech accountable and propose a co-regulatory model drawing from regional experiences.
KW  - disinformation; Philippines; platform accountability; cybercrime law; elections
DO  - 10.2139/ssrn.4312456
ER  -

