JO  - Asian-Pacific Law and Policy Journal
VL  - 22
IS  - 1
SP  - 45
EP  - 78
AB  - Vietnam's Cybersecurity Law of 2018 represents one of Southeast Asia's most comprehensive attempts to regulate online content and platform behavior. This paper examines how the law affects Big Tech self-regulation practices and its implications for freedom of expression. Through interviews with civil society organizations and legal analysis, we document how platforms navigate between compliance with state demands and their own content policies.
KW  - Vietnam; cybersecurity law; internet governance; digital rights; censorship
DO  - 10.2139/ssrn.3891234
