AB  - This comparative study examines regulatory frameworks governing ride-hailing platforms Gojek and Grab across six Southeast Asian countries. We analyze licensing requirements, driver classification, and price regulation mechanisms. The study finds significant regulatory divergence across the region and proposes harmonized framework for platform economy governance in ASEAN.
KW  - ride-hailing; Gojek; Grab; platform regulation; ASEAN; transport
DO  - 10.1016/j.tranpol.2022.01.015
