PY  - 2023
JO  - International Journal of Law and Information Technology
VL  - 31
IS  - 2
SP  - 112
EP  - 135
AB  - TikTok's rapid growth in Thailand has raised significant questions about content moderation and the protection of youth digital rights. This article examines how Thai law addresses platform obligations under the Computer Crimes Act B.E. 2560 and analyzes TikTok's community guidelines in relation to Thai legal standards. We find that platform self-regulation often diverges from local legal requirements, creating governance gaps that disproportionately affect young users' freedom of expression.
KW  - TikTok; Thailand; youth digital rights; content moderation; Computer Crimes Act
DO  - 10.1093/ijlit/eaad012
