AB  - This paper examines the regulatory landscape for blockchain technology adoption in Indonesian financial services. We analyze OJK regulations and their implications for fintech companies seeking to leverage distributed ledger technology. The study identifies key regulatory barriers and proposes a sandbox approach for blockchain innovation in the Indonesian market.
KW  - blockchain; fintech; Indonesia; OJK; financial regulation
