PY  - 2023
JO  - Singapore Academy of Law Journal
VL  - 35
SP  - 456
EP  - 489
AB  - Singapore's Online Safety Act 2022 introduces significant new obligations for social media services regarding harmful online content. This article provides a comprehensive analysis of the Act's provisions, examining how they reshape the relationship between the state, platforms, and users. We assess whether Singapore's approach—combining platform codes of practice with ministerial directions—offers a viable regulatory model for other Southeast Asian jurisdictions seeking to balance safety with freedom of expression online.
KW  - Singapore; Online Safety Act; platform regulation; content moderation; freedom of expression
