VL  - 10
IS  - 3
SP  - 100545
AB  - During the COVID-19 pandemic, Southeast Asian governments used emergency powers to mandate removal of health misinformation from social media platforms. This study examines government-platform cooperation in content moderation across six ASEAN countries and assesses the implications for public health communication and freedom of expression. We find that platform compliance with government takedown requests increased significantly during the pandemic period.
KW  - COVID-19; infodemic; social media; censorship; Southeast Asia; public health
DO  - 10.1016/j.hlpt.2021.06.003
