PY  - 2022
JO  - Journal of Human Rights and Technology
VL  - 8
IS  - 1
SP  - 67
EP  - 94
AB  - Facebook's role in the spread of anti-Rohingya hate speech in Myanmar has prompted intense scrutiny of platform content moderation practices. This article examines the conflicts between Facebook's Community Standards and Myanmar's legal framework, analyzing the platform's compliance with government content removal requests before and after the 2021 military coup. We argue that platform self-regulation failed to prevent the weaponization of social media for human rights abuses and assess the implications for Big Tech governance in authoritarian contexts.
KW  - Facebook; Myanmar; hate speech; Rohingya; platform governance; human rights
