AB  - YouTube's automated Content ID system raises complex questions about platform governance and copyright enforcement across Southeast Asian legal systems. This article examines how YouTube's self-regulatory mechanisms interact with varying national copyright laws in the Philippines, Indonesia, Thailand, and Malaysia. We find that algorithmic content moderation creates systematic disadvantages for creators from the Global South and argue for greater platform transparency and regional regulatory coordination.
KW  - YouTube; copyright; Content ID; Southeast Asia; platform governance; algorithmic moderation
