JO  - Computer Law and Security Review
VL  - 52
SP  - 105923
AB  - This article examines how Twitter/X navigates regulatory demands across ASEAN member states, focusing on government requests for content removal and user data. Drawing on the platform's transparency reports from 2019–2023, we analyze compliance patterns and their relationship to national legal frameworks on freedom of expression. The paper situates platform self-regulation within the broader "ASEAN Way" of non-confrontational governance and assesses emerging trends in regional digital regulation.
KW  - Twitter; ASEAN; social media regulation; transparency; freedom of expression; government requests
